        "n_missing": 0,
        "top_classes": [
          {
            "count": 1,
            "name": "This somewhat heterogeneous sample consists of bands of pure fine-grained to microcrystalline dolomite, alternating with bands of coarser dolomite crystals and subangular aligned quartz grains showing pressure solution texture. There is also a greenish-brown material (clay) scattered throughout the sample in small amounts. Particle size was 0-75 Micrometers. Original ASTER Spectral Library name was jhu.becknic.rock.sedimentary.limestone.fine.limest2.spectrum.txt"
          },
          {
            "count": 1,
            "name": "Ooids in the sample are small (0.5-0.75 mm) with laminar structures largely destroyed by dolomitic recrystallization. Carbonate crystals show a heterogeneous distribution, from microcrystalline to fine medium-grained. Abundant quartz fragments and some altered plagioclase (albite twinning), opaques, carbonaceous material, ferruginous clay, and a brown-green to colorless micaceous mineral are also present. Particle size was 0 - 75 Micrometers. Original ASTER Spectral Library name was jhu.becknic.rock.sedimentary.limestone.fine.limest7.spectrum.txt"
          }
        ]
      },
